external_knowledge:
Survived refers to passengers who did not die during the journey; Paid more than 50 units means an average fare greater than 50; 
Sail in the same class means passengers with the same ticket class (e.g., 1st, 2nd, 3rd); 
From the same port means passengers who embarked from the same port (e.g., Cherbourg, Queenstown, Southampton).

sql:
SELECT class_name
FROM ticket_classes
WHERE average_fare > 300;

SELECT DISTINCT pclass 
FROM passengers 
ORDER BY pclass;
